#. [object]
#: Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3377
msgid "Life of Uteaqniq Zei"
msgstr "Vida de Uteaqniq Zei"

#. [object]
#: Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:3382
msgid ""
"Uteaqniq Zei knew everything about business. After a miserable childhood in "
"the streets of the imperial capital of Wesnoth, he spent most of his teenage "
"years transforming stolen eggs or smashed glass into warm meals.\n"
"\n"
"        During a brief mission in the 2nd legion, he learnt to trade and "
"mastered the art of finding terrific deals. But the gloom of military life "
"was incompatible with his desire of adventure. He therefore resigned to join "
"a small trading company in the west.\n"
"\n"
"        Sometime after arriving at Idaamub, Zei met the Dunefolks. He "
"quickly became aware that they had more to offer than exotic weapons and "
"jewels that other companies could not buy. By chance, he had seen the "
"Dunefolks manipulating materials looking like eggshells, thick as a human "
"hand and shining splendidly. Judging by the way they were bending them, Zei "
"estimated they were harder than granite. If he could get enough of them to "
"pave the floor of the house of some fortunate patrician, he would earn quite "
"a sum. \n"
"\n"
"        Fortunately for Zei, the shells were worthless to the Dunefolks, who "
"were happy to get rid of them. Their joy doubled when Zei offered them in "
"exchange the same objects many companies had offered them in exchange for "
"their weapons and jewels. \n"
"\n"
"        With time, the Dunefolks made Uteaqniq one of their privileged "
"associate, and even went as far as giving him some weapons, despite having "
"refused other interested partners. Uteaqniq’s wealth never stopped growing "
"during those time, and at the time of the punishment of Dunefolks, he had "
"become one of the most fortunate citizens of Idaamub."
msgstr ""
"Uteaqniq Zei sabía todo sobre negocios. Después de una infancia miserable en "
"las calles de la capital imperial de Wesnoth, pasó la mayoría de sus años "
"adolescentes transformando huevos robados o vidrio roto en comidas "
"calientes.\n"
"\n"
"        Durante una breve misión en la 2ª legión, aprendió a comerciar y "
"dominó el arte de encontrar ofertas increíbles. Pero la oscuridad de la vida "
"militar era incompatible con su deseo de aventura. Por lo tanto, renunció "
"para unirse a una pequeña compañía comercial en el oeste.\n"
"\n"
"        Algún tiempo después de llegar a Idaamub, Zei conoció a los "
"Barjanes. Rápidamente se dio cuenta de que tenían más que ofrecer que armas "
"exóticas y joyas que otras compañías no podían comprar. Por casualidad, "
"había visto a los Barjanes manipulando materiales que parecían cascarones de "
"huevos, gruesos como una mano humana y brillando espléndidamente. A juzgar "
"por la forma en que los doblaban, Zei estimó que eran más duros que el "
"granito. Si pudiera obtener suficientes para pavimentar el piso de la casa "
"de algún patricio afortunado, ganaría una buena suma. \n"
"\n"
"        Afortunadamente para Zei, las conchas no valían nada para los "
"Barjanes, que estaban felices de deshacerse de ellas. Su alegría se duplicó "
"cuando Zei les ofreció a cambio los mismos objetos que muchas compañías les "
"habían ofrecido a cambio de sus armas y joyas. \n"
"\n"
"        Con el tiempo, los Barjanes hicieron de Uteaqniq uno de sus "
"asociados privilegiados, e incluso llegaron a darle algunas armas, a pesar "
"de haber rechazado a otros socios interesados. La riqueza de Uteaqniq nunca "
"dejó de crecer durante esos tiempos, y en el momento del castigo de los "
"Barjanes, se había convertido en uno de los ciudadanos más afortunados de "
"Idaamub."

