#. [object]
#: Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:4327
msgid "History of the Dunefolks"
msgstr "Historia de los Barjanes"

#. [object]
#: Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:4332
msgid ""
"A long time ago, a company of imperial merchants looking for new routes to "
"the other side of the Green Mountains were surprised to discover a huge "
"community living in the Fire Cliffs.\n"
"\n"
"        The impressive weapons and jewels possessed by those humble "
"troglodytes were beyond belief but the Dunefolks, self-sufficient, saw no "
"reason to trade items of value against the trinkets that were offering the "
"imperial merchants.\n"
"\n"
"        During the following years, the merchants vainly tried to convince "
"the Dunefolks, until a company presented them a roll of shimmering fabric "
"brought, with other goods, from the imperial capital city. The Dunefolks "
"were immediately bewitched by the presented model and gladly agreed to sell "
"some of their best weapons to the astonished merchants.\n"
"\n"
"        With their eyes full of golden images, the caravan rushed back to "
"the capital city and, once back, prepared in the highest secret, loads of "
"fabrics to barter with the Dunefolks. Unfortunately for them, the capital "
"city and the Dunefolks were connected by a 730-league-long dangerous "
"commercial route, often scene of goblin attacks.\n"
"\n"
"        Fate then decided the caravan to be captured and the goblin to learn "
"the interest of the Dunefolks to the fabrics of their prisoners. Goblins had "
"given up trading with the Dunefolks centuries before and diligent goblins "
"therefore assessed the loots.\n"
"\n"
"        In six months, the small group of goblins evaded on numerous "
"occasions Legion patrols and carried many rolls of fabrics but arriving at "
"the Fire Cliffs, they realized they had been outstripped by an independent "
"merchant named Uteaqniq Zei. The Dunefolks were still interested in goblin’s "
"goods but, because of the commercial relation tied with Uteaqniq, were not "
"willing to batter them against their items anymore. Goblins were forced to "
"retreat with a trivial quantity of baskets, incomplete necklaces, and cast-"
"off mining tools in exchange for their goods formerly so precious.\n"
"\n"
"        Goblins never forgot Uteaqniq Zei and decided that, many years "
"later, they would have their revenge."
msgstr ""
"Hace mucho tiempo, una compañía de mercaderes imperiales buscando nuevas "
"rutas al otro lado de las Montañas Verdes se sorprendió al descubrir una "
"enorme comunidad viviendo en los Acantilados de Fuego.\n"
"\n"
"        Las impresionantes armas y joyas poseídas por esos humildes "
"trogloditas eran increíbles pero los Barjanes, autosuficientes, no veían "
"razón para intercambiar ítems de valor contra las baratijas que ofrecían los "
"mercaderes imperiales.\n"
"\n"
"        Durante los años siguientes, los mercaderes intentaron en vano "
"convencer a los Barjanes, hasta que una compañía les presentó un rollo de "
"tela reluciente traída, con otros bienes, de la capital imperial. Los "
"Barjanes quedaron inmediatamente hechizados por el modelo presentado y "
"accedieron gustosamente a vender algunas de sus mejores armas a los "
"mercaderes asombrados.\n"
"\n"
"        Con los ojos llenos de imágenes doradas, la caravana se apresuró de "
"vuelta a la capital y, una vez de regreso, preparó en el mayor secreto, "
"cargas de telas para truequear con los Barjanes. Desafortunadamente para "
"ellos, la capital y los Barjanes estaban conectados por una ruta comercial "
"peligrosa de 730 leguas de largo, a menudo escenario de ataques goblin.\n"
"\n"
"        El destino decidió entonces que la caravana fuera capturada y que "
"los goblin aprendieran el interés de los Barjanes por las telas de sus "
"prisioneros. Los goblin habían renunciado a comerciar con los Barjanes "
"siglos antes y por lo tanto goblins diligentes evaluaron los botines.\n"
"\n"
"        En seis meses, el pequeño grupo de goblins evadió en numerosas "
"ocasiones patrullas de la Legión y llevó muchos rollos de telas pero al "
"llegar a los Acantilados de Fuego, se dieron cuenta de que habían sido "
"superados por un mercader independiente llamado Uteaqniq Zei. Los Barjanes "
"aún estaban interesados en los bienes de los goblin pero, debido a la "
"relación comercial atada con Uteaqniq, no estaban dispuestos a truequearlos "
"contra sus ítems más. Los goblin se vieron obligados a retirarse con una "
"cantidad trivial de cestas, collares incompletos y herramientas de minería "
"desechadas a cambio de sus bienes anteriormente tan preciosos.\n"
"\n"
"        Los goblin nunca olvidaron a Uteaqniq Zei y decidieron que, muchos "
"años después, tendrían su venganza."

#. [object]
#: Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:4347
msgid "From swords to shares"
msgstr "De espadas a acciones"

#. [object]
#: Legends_of_Idaamub/utils/item_list.cfg:4352
msgid ""
"Hcui Loazfa was carrying the torch of his beloved 10th Legion for twenty "
"years already. Under his command, the Legion had become one of the most "
"talented military unit of all time, coming through the challenge of the "
"pacification of Xvaenc’s peninsula and the War of Legions with minor "
"losses.\n"
"\n"
"        But having vanquished, to some exceptions, its most famous enemies, "
"the Legion suddenly fell into an identity crisis. The empire to which it had "
"sworn allegiance was not anymore and the quarrels in its ranks were more "
"numerous than ever. ''Nothing is more terrible than an army with no enemy to "
"fight.'', noted then down a frustrated Loazfa in his chronicles. ''I have "
"seen enough blood in my life, and I could satisfy myself with an acre of "
"land, a spade and mule for the rest of my life but what will I do with all "
"this enthusiastic young people?''\n"
"\n"
"        The first day of the new year, talking to an assembly of chilled-to-"
"the-bone worried men, Hcui Loazfa announced that the 10th Legion would not "
"be able to subsist like that. Food was short, especially because of too few "
"farmers and too many legionnaires. He then offered his men bet on good "
"fortune and start back from zero and create a new kingdom.\n"
"\n"
"        Immediately, Loafza was asked to take the throne of Idaamub but he "
"gracefully declined the offer, arguing that the new kingdom will need an "
"army and that it was his intentions to guide it through the difficult times "
"awaiting. Refugees from other regions were already flocking, trying to "
"protect themselves from the chaos that was raging in Sob Plain. But he was "
"suspecting other visitors, this time less benevolent, will soon join them as "
"soon as the news of Idaamub’s good fortune will spread."
msgstr ""
"Hcui Loazfa llevaba la antorcha de su amada 10ª Legión por veinte años ya. "
"Bajo su mando, la Legión se había convertido en una de las unidades "
"militares más talentosas de todos los tiempos, superando el desafío de la "
"pacificación de la península de Xvaenc y la Guerra de Legiones con pérdidas "
"menores.\n"
"\n"
"        Pero habiendo vencido, con algunas excepciones, a sus enemigos más "
"famosos, la Legión cayó repentinamente en una crisis de identidad. El "
"imperio al que había jurado lealtad ya no existía y las peleas en sus filas "
"eran más numerosas que nunca. «Nada es más terrible que un ejército sin "
"enemigo que combatir.», anotó entonces un frustrado Loazfa en sus crónicas. "
"«He visto suficiente sangre en mi vida, y podría satisfacerme con un acre de "
"tierra, una pala y una mula para el resto de mi vida pero ¿qué haré con toda "
"esta gente joven entusiasta?»\n"
"\n"
"        El primer día del nuevo año, hablando a una asamblea de hombres "
"preocupados helados hasta los huesos, Hcui Loazfa anunció que la 10ª Legión "
"no podría subsistir así. La comida era escasa, especialmente por muy pocos "
"granjeros y demasiados legionarios. Luego ofreció a sus hombres apostar por "
"la buena fortuna y empezar de cero y crear un nuevo reino.\n"
"\n"
"        Inmediatamente, se le pidió a Loazfa que tomara el trono de Idaamub "
"pero declinó graciosamente la oferta, argumentando que el nuevo reino "
"necesitará un ejército y que era su intención guiarlo a través de los "
"tiempos difíciles que aguardaban. Refugiados de otras regiones ya se "
"agolpaban, tratando de protegerse del caos que rugía en la Llanura de Sob. "
"Pero sospechaba que otros visitantes, esta vez menos benevolentes, se "
"unirían pronto a ellos tan pronto como se extendiera la noticia de la buena "
"fortuna de Idaamub."

